**[1847, 03-29] Ms.B.1.6.3.23**

Haughton to May Jr. {Some in {u}BAA{/u}}

Various subjects; Evang Alliance, Liberty Party, Irish confederation. …
“I am glad to find that the Papers I send you occasionally afford you
some pleasure, they go across the boiling waters to tell you that I wish
always to have you in remembrance. Your short visit here, made us
personally acquainted & that acquaintance has given us mutual pleasure.
If we never meet again on earth, it will be pleasant to us both to feel
that we have met & that we are laboring together in much unity of
feeling, for benefit of our race. …” Has chatted with Elihu Burritt,
whose arguments in favor of the Liberty Party failed to convince him.


